body.description: The instinctive action of sucking helps to calm and soothe babies and all parents know there’s nothing more wonderful than a calm, content baby. Little mouths don’t always hold onto heavy baby pacifiers which means parents often need to replace the pacifier in their baby’s mouth every few minutes. Our Ultra-Light Silicone pacifier is our lightest ever pacifier and is light enough to stay put in baby’s mouth for longer helping babies to stay calmer, soothed and happier for longer. As the symmetrical silicone baglet is fully reversible, there is no ‘wrong’ side-up so the pacifier will always be placed correctly in your baby’s mouth, even when they put it in their mouth themselves. The curved shield sits comfortably between baby’s chin and nose and the holes in each side allow extra air flow and prevent the build-up of moisture which helps to protect baby’s delicate skin against irritation. The smooth surface of silicone is very easy to clean and won’t absorb stains and odors. The hygienic, anti-static properties prevent dust from settling and as it has a one-piece design, it is really easy to clean - simply pop in a sterilizer, wash by hand or in the top shelf of the dishwasher. We recommend that you replace the pacifier every month and always at the first signs of damage or weakness. We recommend against prolonged pacifier use over 24 months and stopping pacifier use when your child is older than 36 months *From an independent study in July 2021 of 416 moms with a 0-36m child, who are currently using a Tommee Tippee® pacifier: • *99% of moms would recommend a Tommee Tippee pacifier • *97% of moms say a Tommee Tippee pacifier helped settle baby • *93% of moms say babies love their Tommee Tippee pacifier • 97.5% of babies accept a Tommee Tippee pacifier Warning! Do not tie pacifier around child’s neck as it presents a strangulation danger.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: A weight off your mind Pacifiers are a brilliant way to keep your baby calm and content. Until they drop out. Then the constant task of retrieving and replacing is exhausting and draining for both of you! To keep bad moods at bay, we’ve created our lightest pacifier yet. Designed to stay put in your baby’s mouth, our Ultra-Light silicone pacifier can help everyone stay calmer and happier for longer.

Symmetrical design The symmetrical, soft silicone baglet is fully reversible and has no ‘wrong’ side-up so the pacifier will always be placed correctly in your baby’s mouth, even when baby puts the pacifier in their mouth themselves. Acceptance guaranteed Accepted by 97.5% of babies**, our Ultra- Light pacifiers are made from 100% medical-grade silicone. Silicone is a soft and flexible but extremely durable material. Love by moms and babies, our pacifiers help to settle baby with 99% of moms recommending to others. ** Silky-soft Made from super-soft 100% medical-grade silicone, this silky-smooth pacifier gives it a skin-like feel and texture, so it feels familiar in baby’s mouth. Silicone is a soft and flexible but extremely durable material which is taste-free and won’t retain any stains or odors.

Ultimate comfort The pacifier shield curves at the top and the bottom to ensure that it sits comfortably between baby’s chin and nose. The holes in the shield allow extra air flow and prevent the build-up of moisture thereby helping to protect baby’s delicate skin against irritation. Available in different age stages The Ultra-Light pacifier is suitable for use from birth and is available in two age stages. The 0-6-month size features a smaller nipple and shield for tiny mouths and noses. As your baby grows, you can switch to the 6-18m pacifier which offers the same benefits but with a larger nipple and shield. Dust-free & easy to clean Hygienic, anti-static properties help prevent dust from settling on this pacifier, so you know it’s safe to put in baby’s mouth. The one-piece design is simple to wash in hot, soapy water, pop in your sterilizer or top shelf of your dishwasher.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Only Pacifier My Kids Would Use
reviews.reviewText: These are honestly amazing pacifiers. While they are a bit pricier than their competitors, these are durable and the colors are always beautiful. They absolutely are lightweight and don't cause my baby to strain to hold them in or use their hands. Also made for easy nights as they didn't fall out as soon as they drifted off to sleep. They are quite durable and easy to clean. No tough creases or holes, no risk of the tips falling off as it is all one piece.

reviews.reviewText: My breastfed baby refused all pacifiers except the bibs pacifiers but she couldn’t hold the bibs in her mouth and would get mad every time her pacifier would fall out, I tried so many brands and different nipple shapes and she wouldn’t touch any of them, while looking for new ones to try I came across these and saw all the reviews saying how good they were and let me tell you they are truly magic, not only do the stay in her mouth but she accepted them immediately and LOVES them!! They are so lightweight and easy to clean since they are one solid piece of silicone! I would highly recommend these to anyone with a breastfed baby or anyone whose baby struggles to keep a pacifier in!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The best bink!
reviews.reviewText: These pacifiers are the only kind my daughter would use 3 years ago, so when we had our son we tried them with him, too. The angle makes it so it’s harder to fall out of their mouth like some we tried, making them perfect for little babies who can’t put the binky in by themselves yet. We spend a lot less time popping it back into his mouth than any other brand we tried. They soothe him instantly. I would definitely recommend trying these before wasting money on any other type of pacifier.

reviews.reviewText: first, all babies are different and i recognize that. however, if your baby will take these, your life will be far easier. we have tried a ton of different pacifiers for our little guy and this one is by far the easiest to clean and the most durable. the only downside is that they don’t glow in the dark like the dr. browns ones, but i’m fine with it for the cleanliness factor. other pacifiers have the little cover over the “nipple” part, and they can be SO difficult to get completely dry. i have a hint of PPA, so knowing that his pacifiers are completely clean and dry has really helped me!
